        <lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Sep 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://whale-dolphin.github.io/en/page/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><item>
            <title>About</title>
            <link>https://whale-dolphin.github.io/en/about/</link>
            <pubDate>Thu, 26 Sep 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <guid>https://whale-dolphin.github.io/en/about/</guid>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;Hey there, stranger. I&amp;rsquo;m Whale Dolphin (鲸鲵) — a name taken from a line in &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;The Rhapsody of the Goddess of the Luo River&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;: &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Whales and salamanders surge alongside the wheel hubs, while water birds soar as escorts.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; Here, whale and salamander refer to male and female aquatic mammals. I gave them their own names too — Whale Fall (鲸落) and Salamander Whisper (鲵笙) — and even named their homes &amp;ldquo;Whale Fall&amp;rsquo;s Pond&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Salamander Whisper&amp;rsquo;s Ocean.&amp;rdquo; I go by Whale Dolphin everywhere online, so if you spot any of these names, that&amp;rsquo;s probably me.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This blog is mostly written for myself. But if you stumbled onto one of my posts and were curious enough to end up here, maybe we&amp;rsquo;re kindred spirits.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m an otaku programmer at heart — I love singing, watching anime, playing gacha games, and I&amp;rsquo;m really into virtual singers and VTubers. Luo Tianyi is my all-time favorite; her voice genuinely keeps me going. Right now I&amp;rsquo;m doing research in speech synthesis, working toward building a model with the expressiveness of a real voice actor. The dream? Creating AI characters that feel as alive as the ones in the anime worlds I love.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
        </item><item>
